node.title: Remote community residents test positive for COVID-19 at Royal Darwin Hospital as outbreak grows by 4
node.description: The Northern Territory has recorded four new COVID-19 cases linked to the current outbreak, including two Timber Creek residents who tested positive at Royal Darwin Hospital.
node.content: ["The Northern Territory has recorded four new COVID-19 cases linked to the current outbreak, including two Timber Creek residents who tested positive at Royal Darwin Hospital.", "The NT recorded a total number of 11 cases overnight.\u00a0", "Of those, five are from a recent repatriation flight from South Africa.\u00a0", "One is an air crew member from a recent London flight, who was in quarantine and not infectious in the\u00a0community.\u00a0", "One new case was picked up in home quarantine in Darwin.\u00a0", "The remaining four cases are linked to the Katherine cluster, bringing the total number of cases to 94.", "One was a woman in her 20s who was a close contact and in Howard Springs quarantine facility.", "Another was a male teenager who was a resident in one of the high-risk streets in Katherine East. He was being transferred to Howard Springs.", "Two more cases linked to the Katherine cluster were confirmed at the Royal Darwin Hospital (RDH): a woman in her 30s and her son aged under 10.", "The pair are residents from Timber Creek, who passed through Katherine earlier this week to attend a scheduled surgery at RDH.", "Acting Chief Minister Nicole Manison said the pair had caught the bus to Darwin from Katherine.", "Ms Manison said a list of exposure sites linked to the mother and son from Timber Creek would\u00a0be released later today.", "\"We are doing the contact tracing now and these details will be released as soon as possible today,\" she said.", "There were 2,700 COVID-19 tests taken in the Northern Territory over the past 24 hours, she said.", "The close contact number is at 184.", "More to come.\u00a0"]
